article.description: — Bryce Daley had 17 points and nine assists as UMass Lowell beat Albany 79-71 on Friday night.
article.headline: Daley leads UMass Lowell past Albany 79-71
article.linkText: Daley leads UMass Lowell past Albany 79-71
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- — Bryce Daley had 17 points and nine assists as UMass Lowell beat Albany 79-71 on Friday night. Kalil Thomas had 14 points for UMass Lowell (8-9, 7-6 America East Conference). Darion Jordan-Thomas added 12 points, nine rebounds and three blocks. UMass Lowell posted a season-high 21 assists. UMass Lowell totaled 53 second-half points, a season high for the team. Antonio Rizzuto scored a career-high 25 points for the Great Danes (4-7, 4-5). Kellon Taylor added 13 points. Chuck Champion had 12 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
